00:12:21.370 --> 00:12:22.320 align:middle line:90%


00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:24.480 align:middle line:84%
We wanted to share some of
the unexamined assumptions

00:12:24.480 --> 00:12:27.240 align:middle line:84%
that we found in our
own lives as we've

00:12:27.240 --> 00:12:29.670 align:middle line:90%
become engaged in this work.

00:12:29.670 --> 00:12:34.110 align:middle line:84%
I, for instance, know that an
unexamined assumption that I

00:12:34.110 --> 00:12:36.950 align:middle line:84%
was working with for a
long time was that if I can

00:12:36.950 --> 00:12:40.270 align:middle line:84%
afford to buy
something, then I should

00:12:40.270 --> 00:12:43.070 align:middle line:90%
just go ahead and do that.

00:12:43.070 --> 00:12:44.960 align:middle line:84%
Linked to that
was the assumption

00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:50.760 align:middle line:84%
that whatever I chose to do
was free of adverse affect

00:12:50.760 --> 00:12:52.250 align:middle line:90%
on other people.

00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:55.210 align:middle line:84%
One of them that comes up
for me is that if I work hard

00:12:55.210 --> 00:12:58.460 align:middle line:84%
and I'm a positive thinker,
I'll somehow not have

00:12:58.460 --> 00:13:01.180 align:middle line:90%
to deal with racism and sexism.

00:13:01.180 --> 00:13:02.330 align:middle line:84%
I think there's
another prevalent

00:13:02.330 --> 00:13:05.200 align:middle line:84%
assumption that opportunity
exists for everybody.

00:13:05.200 --> 00:13:07.320 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't get
ahead, it's probably

00:13:07.320 --> 00:13:10.230 align:middle line:84%
because we haven't worked hard
enough or tried hard enough.

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:12.190 align:middle line:90%
Or we're not smart enough.

00:13:12.190 --> 00:13:14.780 align:middle line:84%
So we'd actually like to
give you an opportunity

00:13:14.780 --> 00:13:17.420 align:middle line:84%
to look and see some of the
assumptions that are playing

00:13:17.420 --> 00:13:20.810 align:middle line:84%
out in your own lives, the
assumptions that maybe exist

00:13:20.810 --> 00:13:24.360 align:middle line:84%
in your thinking that you
haven't previously looked at

00:13:24.360 --> 00:13:28.100 align:middle line:84%
but are the assumptions that are
leading you into-- particularly

00:13:28.100 --> 00:13:31.430 align:middle line:84%
these-- the assumptions that
lead you into behaviors you

00:13:31.430 --> 00:13:33.730 align:middle line:84%
don't want,
behaviors that aren't

00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:37.050 align:middle line:84%
consistent with a
sustainable and a just

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.830 align:middle line:90%
and a fulfilling future.

00:13:38.830 --> 00:13:41.640 align:middle line:84%
So really, in conversation,
what can you find?

00:13:41.640 --> 00:13:43.010 align:middle line:84%
What are the
unexamined assumptions

00:13:43.010 --> 00:13:45.450 align:middle line:84%
that now you can
become aware of that

00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:49.820 align:middle line:84%
are driving our behavior here
together in the modern world?

00:13:49.820 --> 00:13:52.520 align:middle line:84%
One assumption
is the expectation

00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:55.720 align:middle line:84%
that government and leaders
will take care of the problems

00:13:55.720 --> 00:13:59.410 align:middle line:84%
that we're witnessing
and learning about here.

00:13:59.410 --> 00:14:02.490 align:middle line:84%
And another one is
just kind of as adults

00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:06.840 align:middle line:84%
that we are defined by
what we do in the world,

00:14:06.840 --> 00:14:11.230 align:middle line:84%
especially on a
professional level.

00:14:11.230 --> 00:14:13.260 align:middle line:84%
One of them was we think
we are doing something,

00:14:13.260 --> 00:14:16.270 align:middle line:84%
but we are not
doing nearly enough.

00:14:16.270 --> 00:14:21.412 align:middle line:84%
And another one is also science
and technology will save us.

00:14:21.412 --> 00:14:23.740 align:middle line:84%
Are two unexamined
assumptions were

00:14:23.740 --> 00:14:26.190 align:middle line:84%
that I'm a separate
individual, that, like, we're

00:14:26.190 --> 00:14:28.130 align:middle line:90%
somehow not connected.

00:14:28.130 --> 00:14:31.170 align:middle line:84%
And our other one was
that we can conquer life,

00:14:31.170 --> 00:14:33.210 align:middle line:90%
that we can master our domain.

00:14:33.210 --> 00:14:35.930 align:middle line:90%


00:14:35.930 --> 00:14:38.930 align:middle line:84%
This distinction of
unconscious, unexamined

00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:41.720 align:middle line:84%
assumptions, for me,
is really the most

00:14:41.720 --> 00:14:43.560 align:middle line:90%
powerful part of the symposium.

00:14:43.560 --> 00:14:45.590 align:middle line:84%
Every time I start
thinking about it,

00:14:45.590 --> 00:14:48.210 align:middle line:84%
I discover yet another
unexamined assumption

00:14:48.210 --> 00:14:50.570 align:middle line:90%
that's got hold of me.

00:14:50.570 --> 00:14:54.040 align:middle line:84%
And what I love about it is
that when you identify them,

00:14:54.040 --> 00:14:56.210 align:middle line:84%
they begin to lose
their grip on your life.

00:14:56.210 --> 00:14:59.140 align:middle line:84%
We're caught in unconscious,
unexamined assumptions.

00:14:59.140 --> 00:15:00.760 align:middle line:90%
More is better.

00:15:00.760 --> 00:15:02.140 align:middle line:90%
There's not enough to go around.

00:15:02.140 --> 00:15:04.030 align:middle line:90%
If you read it, it's true.

00:15:04.030 --> 00:15:05.450 align:middle line:84%
You can't really
make a difference.

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:06.420 align:middle line:90%
It's too big.

00:15:06.420 --> 00:15:09.230 align:middle line:84%
All of these unconscious,
unexamined assumptions

00:15:09.230 --> 00:15:12.420 align:middle line:84%
kind of paralyze us and keep
us from making a difference

00:15:12.420 --> 00:15:14.970 align:middle line:84%
with our life, really
getting into action,

00:15:14.970 --> 00:15:17.890 align:middle line:84%
really knowing that
we matter and that we

00:15:17.890 --> 00:15:19.850 align:middle line:90%
can change the world.

00:15:19.850 --> 00:15:22.580 align:middle line:84%
See if you can identify
some unexamined assumptions

00:15:22.580 --> 00:15:23.880 align:middle line:90%
of your own.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.750 align:middle line:10%
Look in several areas--
your beliefs about the world

00:15:26.750 --> 00:15:31.430 align:middle line:10%
around you, about other people,
about yourself, about purpose

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:33.380 align:middle line:10%
and meaning in life.

00:15:33.380 --> 00:15:36.460 align:middle line:84%
And when you've written down
several unexamined assumptions,

00:15:36.460 --> 00:15:38.770 align:middle line:90%
come on back.

